body:
r? @huonw

(rust_highfive has picked a reviewer for you, use r? to override)
You could document the trait itself rather than this specific implementation of it, no?

I don't mind documenting the trait. I was thinking there weren't any examples of traits being documented directly: [`Iterator`](http://doc.rust-lang.org/std/iter/trait.Iterator.html) and [`AsSlice`](http://doc.rust-lang.org/std/slice/trait.AsSlice.html) for example though I guess [`IteratorExt`](http://doc.rust-lang.org/std/iter/trait.IteratorExt.html) is a trait. I can shift.
Yes, we usually document the trait, not the specific implementation. This seems good though, thanks! would you mind squashing? r=me after
Got a few left but sure.
Do you want me to just wait until you've got more? I assumed this was ready, if not, I'm happy to hold off.

Yeah. I've got another commit incoming. I'll squash after. I got most everything, maybe skipping deprecated and possibly a few unstable.

I'll change the title from WIP when it's ready.
@steveklabnik This depends on https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/22076 merging. It won't pass `make check` until then.

@steveklabnik Seems pretty good. Needs https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/22076 though so gotta wait until that lands. I'll do r= after that merges and `make check` passes. Ready to commit besides all that though.
Thanks! Not rolling up since this is a pretty big change.
Looks like one example is wrong.
Squash and amend is just fine.

Huh...this was a rebase onto @huonw 's https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/22254 so I could use his renamed `MAX` and `MIN` and not have to rebase later to pick them up...not sure if this is okay or not...

The rest of the commits just kinda came along for the ride...
Passes `make check`. I assume all those commits will disappear once the bors rollup lands...
Rebased this commit back to tip. Should be mergeable. Didn't retest.
no rollup as this is a big diff
